# Pyth Price Feeds Skill

Activate on: "price feeds", "Pyth oracle", "on-chain prices", "price oracle", "Hermes", "IPyth",
"Pyth MCP", "list all feeds", "discover feed IDs", "get_symbols", "mcp.pyth.network",
"circuit breaker", "perps oracle", "perpetuals", "funding rate", "liquidation bot",
"price keeper", "migrate from Chainlink", "upgradeable proxy", "Express Relay", "batch prices"

## Workflow
1. Detect stack: `foundry.toml` → Foundry | `hardhat.config.*` → Hardhat | `Anchor.toml` → Anchor
2. Install: `npm install @pythnetwork/pyth-sdk-solidity` (EVM) or `@pythnetwork/hermes-client` (off-chain)
3. Foundry remappings: `@pythnetwork/pyth-sdk-solidity/=node_modules/@pythnetwork/pyth-sdk-solidity`

## EVM Pull Integration
- Import `IPyth` + `PythStructs` from SDK
- Store `IPyth pyth` in constructor with Pyth contract address
- Accept `bytes[] calldata priceUpdate` in functions needing prices
- `uint fee = pyth.getUpdateFee(priceUpdate)` → `pyth.updatePriceFeeds{value: fee}(priceUpdate)` → `pyth.getPriceNoOlderThan(feedId, maxAge)`
- Price struct: `{int64 price, uint64 conf, int32 expo, uint publishTime}` — real = price × 10^expo

## Critical Rules
- ALWAYS `getPriceNoOlderThan` — never `getPriceUnsafe` in production
- ALWAYS dynamic fee via `getUpdateFee` — never hardcode
- ALWAYS convert fixed-point: price × 10^expo
- Lending: collateral = price - conf, debt = price + conf

## Chain Addresses
- Ethereum: `0x4305FB66699C3B2702D4d05CF36551390A4c69C6`
- Arbitrum/Optimism/Polygon: `0xff1a0f4744e8582DF1aE09D5611b887B6a12925C`
- Base: `0x8250f4aF4B972684F7b336503E2D6dFeDeB1487a`

## Feed ID Discovery (Prefer Dynamic)
- **Pyth MCP** (if available): `get_symbols(query="ETH", asset_type="crypto")`
- **Hermes API**: `GET https://hermes.pyth.network/v2/price_feeds?query=btc&asset_type=crypto`
- **Hardcoded**: ETH/USD `0xff61491a...fd0ace` | BTC/USD `0xe62df6c8...415b43`

## Hermes
- REST: `https://hermes.pyth.network/v2/updates/price/latest?ids[]=<feedId>`
- SSE: `https://hermes.pyth.network/v2/updates/price/stream?ids[]=<feedId>`
- Feed catalog: `https://hermes.pyth.network/v2/price_feeds`

## Pyth MCP (Optional)
- Endpoint: `https://mcp.pyth.network/mcp` (Streamable HTTP)
- Tools: `get_symbols`, `get_latest_price`, `get_historical_price`, `get_candlestick_data`
- Complementary to this skill — MCP for discovery, skill for implementation

